ey&rsquo;re eligible for leave but not pay. All Additional Paternity Leave taken after the end of the Statutory Maternity Pay, Maternity Allowance or Statutory Adoption Pay period is unpaid.</p>\n\n<h2>Eligibility</h2>\n\n<p>Employees are eligible if: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>they&rsquo;ve worked for you continuously for at least 26 weeks by the &lsquo;qualifying week&rsquo;</li>\n  <li>they&rsquo;re employed by you the week (Saturday to Sunday) before their leave and or pay starts</li>\n  <li>they are on your payroll and earn at least £107 a week (gross) in an 8 week period </li>\n  <li>their partner has at least 2 weeks left of their maternity or adoption pay (<abbr title=\"Additional Paternity Pay\">APP</abbr> only)</li>\n  <li>their partner signs one of the forms below confirming their maternity or adoption leave or pay is ending</li>\n  <li>they give you the correct notice using the forms below  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The qualifying week is:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the end of the 15th week before the expected week of childbirth</li>\n  <li>the week they were matched with a child by a UK adoption agency (UK adoptions) </li>\n  <li>the time they get official notification from a UK authority that they can adopt from abroad (overseas adoptions)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Notice period</h3>\n\n<p>Employees should give you 8 weeks&rsquo; notice using the forms below (or your own versions). Within 28 days of their request, write confirming what <abbr title=\"Additional Paternity Pay\">APP</abbr> they&rsquo;ll get and their leave start and end dates.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/forms/sc7.pdf\" title=\"Download Form SC7 - for births (PDF, 46KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form SC7 - for births’ (PDF, 46KB)</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/forms/sc8.pdf\" title=\"Download Form SC8 - for UK adoptions (PDF, 45KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form SC8 - for UK adoptions’ (PDF, 45KB)</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/forms/sc9.pdf\" title=\"Download Form SC9 - for overseas adoptions (PDF, 45KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form SC9 - for overseas adoptions’ (PDF, 45KB)</a>  </p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/forms/sc10.pdf\" title=\"Form SC10 - if the mother or adopter dies (PDF, 70KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form SC10 - if the mother or adopter dies’ (PDF, 70KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>If an employee doesn&rsquo;t give you the right amount of notice without a good reason, you can delay the start of leave and the pay period until you&rsquo;ve had acceptable notice. </p>\n\n<h2>Proof you can ask for</h2>\n\n<p>You can ask for:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>proof of the birth or adoption - eg a birth certificate or letter from the adoption agency</li>\n  <li>the contact details of their partner&rsquo;s employer - eg to check when their partner&rsquo;s maternity pay ends</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>They should give this to you within 28 days or they won&rsquo;t qualify for leave or pay. </p>\n\n<h2>Refusing leave or pay</h2>\n\n<p>If an employee doesn&rsquo;t qualify, write to them within 28 days of their request and include form ASPP1. </p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/forms/aspp1.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Form ASPP1 - non-payment of Additional Paternity Pay' (PDF, 45KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form ASPP1 - non-payment of Additional Paternity Pay’ (PDF, 45KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Help with statutory payments</h2>\n\n<p>You can <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/paye/employees/statutory-pay/aspp-calc.htm\" title=\"How to calculate and recover Additional Statutory Paternity Pay\">recover the statutory amounts</a> you&rsquo;ve paid from HM Revenue &amp; Customs or apply for an <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/paye/employees/statutory-pay/funding.htm\" title=\"Statutory payment help from HMRC\">advance payment.</a></p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/helpsheets/e19.pdf\" title=\"Download 'E19 Employer helpbook to Ordinary and Additional Statutory Paternity Pay' (PDF, 745KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘E19 Employer helpbook to Ordinary and Additional Statutory Paternity Pay’ (PDF, 745KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n","alternative_title":"Additional Statutory Paternity Pay and Additional Paternity Leave: employer guide"},"updated_at":"2012-10-26T14:25:52+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Statutory leave and time off","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people%2Ftime-off.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes maternity and paternity leave, holiday entitlement and sick pay","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people%2Ftime-off","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people/time-off"},"parent":{"title":"Employing people","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes pay, contracts and hiring","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Business Link","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/businesslink.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":null,"short_description":null,"type":"legacy_source"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=businesslink","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/businesslink"},"parent":null}],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/paternity-leave-pay-employees.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/paternity-leave-pay-employees","title":"Ordinary Statutory Paternity Pay and Leave: employer guide","format":"guide","details":{"need_id":"B153","business_proposition":true,"description":"Employer guide to Statutory Paternity Pay or Leave - entitlement, eligibility, notice period, forms SC3 and OSPP1, recover statutory pay"},"updated_at":"2012-10-26T14:39:08+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.