aying leave","body":"<p>Leave can&rsquo;t be postponed (delayed) if: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the employer doesn&rsquo;t have a &lsquo;significant reason&rsquo; - eg it would cause serious disruption to the business </li>\n  <li>it&rsquo;s being taken by the father or partner immediately after the birth or adoption of a child </li>\n  <li>it means an employee would no longer qualify for parental leave - eg postponing it until after the child’s 5th birthday </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If it&rsquo;s postponed, the employer: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>must write explaining why within 7 days of the original request </li>\n  <li>suggest a new start date - this must be within 6 months of the requested start date </li>\n  <li>can&rsquo;t change the amount of leave being requested </li>\n</ul>\n"}]},"updated_at":"2012-10-31T13:00:56+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Statutory leave and time off","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people%2Ftime-off.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes maternity and paternity leave, holiday entitlement and sick pay","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people%2Ftime-off","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people/time-off"},"parent":{"title":"Employing people","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes pay, contracts and hiring","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Holidays, time off, sick leave, maternity and paternity leave","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working%2Ftime-off.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes career breaks and the holiday entitlement calculator","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working%2Ftime-off","web_