nal Insurance need to be deducted. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Calculate an employee’s adoption leave and pay using the <a href=\"/maternity-paternity-calculator\" title=\"Maternity and paternity calculator\">maternity and paternity calculator</a>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/helpsheets/e16.pdf\" title=\"Download 'E16 Employer helpbook to Statutory Adoption Pay' (PDF, 745KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘E16 Employer helpbook to Statutory Adoption Pay’ (PDF, 745KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Extra leave or pay</h2>\n\n<p>You can offer more than the statutory amounts if you have a company scheme for adoption leave and pay. You must make sure your scheme&rsquo;s policies are clear and easily accessible to staff. </p>\n\n<h2>Employment rights</h2>\n\n<p>An employee&rsquo;s <a href=\"/employee-rights-when-on-leave\" title=\"Employee right to accrue leave\">employment rights</a> (like the right to pay, holidays and returning to a job) are protected during adoption leave.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/adoption-leave-pay-employees/eligibility","slug":"eligibility","order":2,"title":"Eligibility","body":"\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Some employees won’t qualify for both leave and pay.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Statutory Adoption Leave</h2>\n\n<p>Employees must: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>have worked for you continuously for at least 26 weeks by the week they were matched with a child (known as the &lsquo;matching week&rsquo;) </li>\n  <li>give you the <a href=\"/adoption-leave-pay-employees/notice-period\" title=\"Notice period\">correct notice</a></li>\n  <li>be classed as an <a href=\"/employment-status/employee\" title=\"employment status\">employee</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>They don&rsquo;t have to give you proof of the adoption unless you request it. </p>\n\n<h2>Statutory Adoption Pay</h2>\n\n<p>Employees must: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>have worked for you continuously for at least