l amount, eg for a daily rate.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>When to start paying <abbr title=\"Statutory Sick Pay\">SSP</abbr></h2>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Statutory Sick Pay\">SSP</abbr> is paid when the employee is sick for 4 days in a row (including non-working days). You start paying <abbr title=\"Statutory Sick Pay\">SSP</abbr> from the fourth day (if they normally work that day).  </p>\n\n<h3>Exception</h3>\n\n<p>You don&rsquo;t usually pay <abbr title=\"Statutory Sick Pay\">SSP</abbr> for the first 3 qualifying days unless they&rsquo;ve been off sick and getting <abbr title=\"Statutory Sick Pay\">SSP</abbr> within the last 8 weeks. </p>\n\n<h2>When to stop paying <abbr title=\"Statutory Sick Pay\">SSP</abbr></h2>\n\n<p>Usually <abbr title=\"Statutory Sick Pay\">SSP</abbr> stops when the employee comes back to work or no longer <a href=\"/sick-leave-pay-employees/eligibility-and-form-ssp1\" title=\"Eligibility\">qualifies</a>.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/helpsheets/e14.pdf\" title=\"Download 'E14 Employer helpbook to Statutory Sick Pay' (PDF, 745KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘E14 Employer helpbook to Statutory Sick Pay’ (PDF, 745KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Record keeping</h2>\n\n<p>You must keep records for HM Revenue &amp; Customs, including:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>all sickness periods lasting at least 4 days</li>\n  <li>your <abbr title=\"Statutory Sick Pay\">SSP</abbr> payments</li>\n  <li>any <abbr title=\"Statutory Sick Pay\">SSP</abbr> you <a href=\"/sick-leave-pay-employees/help-with-sick-pay\" title=\"Recover SSP\">recover</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You can use form SSP2 to keep these records. </p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/forms/ssp2.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Form SSP2, Statutory Sick Pay record sheet' (PDF, 135KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form SSP2, Statutory Sick Pay record sheet’ (PDF, 135KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/sick-leave-pay-employees/eligibilit