">SSP</abbr> calculator</a> to check eligibility.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Form SSP1</h2>\n\n<p>If an employee isn&rsquo;t eligible you must send them form SSP1 within 7 days of them going off sick. They can apply for <a href=\"/employment-support-allowance\" title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">Employment and Support Allowance</a> instead.</p>\n\n<p>If your employee thinks this is unfair, they can appeal to HM Revenue and Customs. </p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dwp.gov.uk/advisers/claimforms/ssp1.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Form SSP1, employee not entitled to SSP' (PDF, 200KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form SSP1, employee not entitled to <abbr title=\"Statutory Sick Pay\">SSP</abbr>’ (PDF, 200KB)</a><br />\n<a href=\"http://www.dsdni.gov.uk/ssp1_cp.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Form SSP1 - Northern Ireland, employee not entitled to SSP' (PDF, 200KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form SSP1 - Northern Ireland, employee not entitled to <abbr title=\"Statutory Sick Pay\">SSP</abbr>’ (PDF, 200KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Long-term illness</h2>\n\n<p>If you know an employee will be off for more than 28 weeks, you can complete SSP1 in advance. This means they can apply for Employment Support Allowance without delay. </p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/sick-leave-pay-employees/notice-and-fit-notes","slug":"notice-and-fit-notes","order":4,"title":"Notice and fit notes","body":"<h2>Notice</h2>\n\n<p>The employee should tell you they&rsquo;re sick within your own time limit (or 7 days if you don’t have one). You don&rsquo;t have to pay Statutory Sick Pay if they don&rsquo;t meet these time limits. </p>\n\n<p>You can&rsquo;t insist notice is given in person or on a special form. </p>\n\n<h2>Asking for proof</h2>\n\n<p>After 7 days off sick you can ask the employee for a <a href=\"/taking-sick-leave\" title=\"Fit notes\">fit note</a> from their doctor. This used to be called a sick note. </p>\n\n<p>You can&rsquo;t withhold <abbr title=\"Statutory Sic